gitCommit.subject: refactor(app): replace editor actions with page actions, add context‚Äëmenu for history and delete button, remove manual save button
gitCommit.body:
refactor(app): replace editor actions with page actions, add context‚Äëmenu for history and delete button, remove manual save button

- Introduced `PageContextMenu` component to toggle history view and handle clicks outside the menu.
- Moved delete functionality to a dedicated ‚Äúüóë‚Äù button with hover styling; eliminated the explicit ‚ÄúSave‚Äù button and its `saveNode` implementation (auto‚Äësave now handles persistence).
- Added new CSS classes (`pageActions`, `deleteButton`, `contextMenu*`) and updated existing styles accordingly.
- Updated `App.tsx` to use the new UI components and adjusted event handling for node deletion and history toggling.
- refactor(app): simplify SidebarNode hover UI and update asset references
- Removed the hover‚Äëactions container (trash‚ÄØ+‚ÄØmenu buttons) and introduced a single `hoverDeleteButton` that appears on hover to delete a node.
- Updated `SidebarNode.module.css` to reflect the new class, adjusting opacity/transition rules and removing unused styles.
- Adjusted `SidebarNode.tsx` to use the new button, delete the context‚Äëmenu trigger button, and reorder the context‚Äëmenu items (history now appears after a divider).
- These changes streamline the sidebar node interactions and keep the build artifacts in sync.
- refactor(app): move delete and history actions from editor header to sidebar nodes, add hover actions with context menu, update CSS and asset references
- Removed page‚Äëactions UI (delete button & context‚Äëmenu) from App header and its styles.
- Introduced hover actions (trash and menu buttons) in SidebarNode with new CSS classes.
- Added onDeleteNode and onShowHistory callbacks to Sidebar and SidebarNode props.
- Implemented node deletion logic in App.tsx (handling current node cleanup and history navigation).
- Adjusted Sidebar and SidebarNode to pass new callbacks and render hover actions/context menu.
